Being a busy mom, who is constantly on the go I use @hydroxycut to stay on track. Being on the road a lot for my sons travel hockey I am not as active as I have been. Hydroxycut helps support me during these times so I can be the best version of myself everyday. #hydroxycut_partner

Our mini vacation to @greatwolflodge is over and my kids are asking when we are headed back! 

The Lodge has something to do for everyone throughout the day, there is hours of fun! Currently they are doing their Snowland celebration which really put us into the Holiday spirit. Meeting Santa, making crafts, playing games, dancing were just some of the amazing things they offer! 

The water park which was 84-degrees was filled with tube slides, body slides, basketball, lazy river, indoor/ outdoor hot tub, interactive water play, massive water bucket that tips over, jam packed with fun for all ages. We were all laughing ams smiling the entire time! 

They also have mini golf, VR, Rock climbing, rope course bowling and sooo many arcade games! Magiquest which you take a magical wand and go on a quest throughout the lodge, and build a bear, or should I say build a wolf for us! I never heard I’m bored once. Talk about a mom win! 👏🏼 

Food: we know I love my food! They have a bar/ place to grab food inside the water park so no need to leave. They also have food/ ice cream/ treats in the main area near the arcades and a restaurant which was buffet style that we got to enjoy for a dinner, and Dunkin! I always start my morning with a coffee and this was the perfect addition inside the hotel I stayed in my pjs and got to grab dunkin and didn’t have to leave the entire weekend. It was so convenient everything you need is all inside the Lodge!

We can’t thank you enough for making us feel so special during our stay! We celebrated the boys birthdays there as well and they decorated the door and inside with balloons. They really go above and beyond on making your trip as magical and fun as possible! #greatwolflodge
